About this item

  • Smart Home Integration: Seamlessly integrate with your smart home ecosystem. Command your floor's warmth with voice commands or a simple tap on your smartphone.
  • Remote Control: Whether you're in bed or abroad, adjust your floor temperature effortlessly through our intuitive mobile app.
  • Intelligent Scheduling: Customize heating schedules to match your daily routines, ensuring you're greeted with the perfect warmth at any time of the day.
  • Energy Insights: Track and monitor your energy consumption. Our smart thermostat learns your habits and offers suggestions to optimize usage, saving you money without compromising on comfort.
  • Sleek Design: With its modern and minimalist design, it's not just a thermostat—it's a statement piece that complements any interior.
  • Safety & Security: Equipped with advanced safety features, ensuring your home stays warm and risk-free. Plus, with encrypted Wi-Fi connections, your data and preferences are always secure.

How customer reviews and ratings work

Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we don’t use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

    Verified Purchase
    Ordered 2 floor heat thermostats for a reno we're doing before selling the house. Price was about half what the big orange box store wanted for a non wifi product, and we wanted wifi to satisfy potential Gen X and millennial buyers. System has been running for about 6 months but recently the touch function on one of the screens stopped working, although it could still be controlled via the app. Kevin at Drexma in Quebec quickly sent us a new one and we're back in business. Only downside is the fluctuating temperature reading as pointed out in a few other reviews, but honestly it's a minor inconvenience, all 3 thermostats we've used do it so we suspect they all do.
